classes.description:
Override or extend the styles applied to the component.
See [CSS API](#css) below for more details.

color.description: The color of the component. It supports those theme colors that make sense for this component.

component.description:
The component used for the root node.
Either a string to use a HTML element or a component.

disableGutters.description: If `true`, the List Subheader will not have gutters.

disableSticky.description: If `true`, the List Subheader will not stick to the top during scroll.

inset.description: If `true`, the List Subheader will be indented.

descriptions.root: Styles applied to the root element.
descriptions.colorPrimary: Styles applied to the root element if `color="primary"`.
descriptions.colorInherit: Styles applied to the root element if `color="inherit"`.
descriptions.gutters: Styles applied to the inner `component` element if `disableGutters={false}`.
descriptions.inset: Styles applied to the root element if `inset={true}`.
descriptions.sticky: Styles applied to the root element if `disableSticky={false}`.
